                        <bindingDesc>
                            <binding contemporary="unknown">
                                <p>Medieval binding. Brown leather over wooden boards. 4 double raised bands, 2 single raised bands, and endbands. Originally, brass hook and clasp. <locus from="Spine" to="Spine" scheme="other"/>, in white paint: <quote>T? Kempis</quote>; in white paint: <quote>N 2 </quote>; in white paint: <quote>2</quote>; stamped in gold:<quote> A 195</quote>.</p>
                                <p>
                                    <dimensions type="binding">
                                        <height quantity="145" unit="mm"/>
                                        <width quantity="120" unit="mm"/>
                                        <depth quantity="45" unit="mm"/>
                                    </dimensions>
                                </p>
                                <decoNote type="tooling">
                                    <p>Blind tooled decoration consisting of panels, frames and x-shapes.</p>
                                </decoNote>
                                <condition>Leather heavily worn. Spine detached, bands visible underneath. Clasp missing. <locus from="RCI" to="RCI" scheme="other"/>, boards and board attachments visible due to detached flyleaf.</condition>
                            </binding>
                        </bindingDesc>
