                        <msContents>
                            <textLang mainLang="la"/>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="25r" to="32v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Excerpts from Jerome, ep. 22: Ad Eustochium, and ep. 130: Ad Demetriadem</title>
                                <rubric>Excerptum ex epistula beati Iheronimi ad eustochium virginem de virginitate seruanda </rubric>
                                <incipit>AVdi filia filia et vide</incipit>
                                <explicit>quo eternitatis gloria acquiratur et cetera</explicit>
                                <finalRubric>Explicit <del>excep</del> excerptio ex epistula beati iheronimi ad demetriadem virginem </finalRubric>
                                <note>The excerpt of the letter to Demetiades is followed by one paragraph by the same hand which ends with: <quote>hec iheronimus in regula capitulo xiii</quote>.</note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="33r" to="38r" scheme="folios"/>
                                <author>
                                    <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/102617"> Jean Gerson </persName>
                                </author>
                                <title type="desc">Letter to the Celestines</title>
                                <rubric>Incipit epistula magistri Johannis gerson cancellarii <del>pae</del> parisiensis quondam missa prouinciali fratrum celestinorum </rubric>
                                <incipit>UEnerendo in christo patri domino prouinciali celestinorum fratri Johanni bassandi </incipit>
                                <explicit>dum me visitauit benignitas tua mihi iure colenda Bene vale </explicit>
                                <finalRubric>Explicit epistula magistri Iohannis gerson cancellarii parisiensis </finalRubric>
                                <bibl>
                                    <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107339">Glorieux (1960)</title>
                                    <citedRange from="264" to="274" unit="page"/>
                                </bibl>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="38v" to="46v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <author>
                                    <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/102617"> Jean Gerson </persName>
                                </author>
                                <title type="desc">Tractatus pro devotis simplicibus</title>
                                <rubric>Sequuntur documenta pro deuotis simplicibus qualiter se discrete in suis excerciciis habere debeant per magistrum iohannem gerson cancellarium parisiensem </rubric>
                                <incipit>DEus wlt ut sat racionabile obsequium nostrum </incipit>
                                <explicit>confidenciam et diuinam caritatem Sibi laus gloriaque in graciarum actio christi Amen</explicit>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="47r" to="53v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Diagrams and lists</title>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="47r" to="49r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">Five diagrams</title>
                                    <note>
                                        <p> These folios contain five sets of diagrams consisiting of rubrics and keywords placed in blindstamped circles. The circles were probably intended to be outlined in ink or decorated in some other way. The rubrics of the diagrams are as follows: <locus from="47r" to="47r" scheme="folios"/>: <quote>Sequuntur gradus per quos ascenditur ad paradisum si bene per ipsos scit peccator confessus gradatim ascendere</quote>;</p>
                                        <p>
                                            <locus from="47v" to="47v" scheme="folios"/>: <quote>Hic sequuntur gradus consiliorum<gap reason="editorial"/>
                                            </quote>;</p>
                                        <p>
                                            <locus from="48r" to="48r" scheme="folios"/>: <quote>Sequuntur octo beatitudine <del>in</del> iustorum<gap reason="editorial"/>
                                            </quote>;</p>
                                        <p>
                                            <locus from="48v" to="48v" scheme="folios"/>: <quote>Item videatur de septem virtutibus<gap reason="editorial"/>
                                            </quote>;</p>
                                        <p>
                                            <locus from="49r" to="49r" scheme="folios"/>: <quote>Sequuntur septem dotes anime</quote>.</p>
                                        <p>
                                            <locus from="49v" to="50r" scheme="folios"/>: blank.</p>
                                        <p/>
                                    </note>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="50v" to="53v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">Lists of sins and virtues </title>
                                    <note>
                                        <p> These folios consist of several lists mainly focused on sins and virutes with different subdivisions. The two major headings are as follows:</p>
                                        <p>
                                            <locus from="50v" to="50v" scheme="folios"/>: <quote>Incipiunt temptaciones <sic>demones</sic> quibus temptat homines de septem peccatis mortalibus et eorum ramis sic homini seruiens suggerens Dyabolus enim temptans dicit peccatori quod peccet hiis modis</quote>;</p>
                                        <p>
                                            <locus from="51r" to="51r" scheme="folios"/>: <quote>Responsionens sancti angeli quibus premunit confortat et docet humanam fragilitatem cum sacra scriptura qualiter temptaciones et resistere vincere debeat dicens ad hominem non facies Quia scriptum est</quote>. The list on <locus from="51r" to="51r" scheme="folios"/> and the list on <locus from="52r" to="52r" scheme="folios"/> contain references to the Bible in the right margin.</p>
                                        <p>
                                            <locus from="54r" to="56v" scheme="folios"/>: blank.</p>
                                        <p/>
                                    </note>
                                </msItem>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="57r" to="58r" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Excerpts from Jerome, ep. 130: Ad Demetriadem </title>
                                <rubric>Iheronimus ad demetraidem de virginis <sic>conuersacione</sic>
                                </rubric>
                                <incipit>Si vis itaque propositi tui magnitudinem </incipit>
                                <explicit>aduentu gottorum et de t<unclear unit="chars" reason="illegible"/>e iniusso habitatoribus ciuitatis</explicit>
                                <bibl>
                                    <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107168">PL</title>
                                    <citedRange from="30" to="30" unit="volume"/>
                                    <citedRange from="15" to="45" unit="column"/>
                                </bibl>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="58v" to="68r" scheme="folios"/>
                                <author>
                                    <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/102619"> Saint Bonaventure </persName>
                                </author>
                                <title type="desc">Parvum bonum (Regimen conscientiae)</title>
                                <rubric>Incipit paruum bonum Bonauenture</rubric>
                                <incipit>Ecce descripsi tibi eam tripliciter prouerbiorum xxii cum omnis scientia</incipit>
                                <explicit>Nota predicta quibus est fons vite eterne </explicit>
                                <finalRubric>Explicit paruum bonum boneventure Cardinalais et doctoris Deuoti ordinis fratrum minorum </finalRubric>
                                <note>68v: blank.</note>
                                <bibl>
                                    <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107341">Bonaventurae decem opuscula</title>
                                    <citedRange from="1" to="42" unit="page"/>
                                </bibl>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="69r" to="75v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">De motivis dileccionis domini</title>
                                <incipit>De motiuis dileccionis domini possumus distinguere</incipit>
                                <explicit>non secundum nostram deordinatam voluntatem</explicit>
                                <finalRubric>hoc de dileccione</finalRubric>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="75v" to="95v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Collection of shorter sermons</title>
                                <rubric>Item maximus in sermone de sancto stephano pontifice ix<hi rend="super">o</hi> plurima de caritate et dileccione inimicorum et quid sit quod nos ad hoc inducat</rubric>
                                <incipit>Item auctus laudator caritatis dicit vbi caritas est quid est quod</incipit>
                                <explicit>Indisciplinate verberibus ac verbis austerioribus sunt corrigende</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <p>There are several blank leaves scattered through this section, 8 in total.</p>
                                    <p/>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="97r" to="116r" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Tractatus de passione domini</title>
                                <rubric>Tractatus quidam deuotus de passione domini</rubric>
                                <incipit>CRisto in carne passo et vos eadem cogitacione </incipit>
                                <explicit>et in nouissimo locandi instar christi qui dixit Ego sum nouissimus virorum</explicit>
                            </msItem>
                        </msContents>
